# Background Jobs System

Background Jobs handle all deferred work in LexMastery.

They ensure smooth UX.

---

# Product Vision

Background jobs must:

- run heavy tasks off main thread
- schedule retries automatically
- handle offline queues
- precompute AI outputs
- manage delayed tasks reliably

---

# Architecture

JobController

↓

JobQueueManager

↓

JobProcessor

↓

Worker Engine

↓

Local Queue + Remote Scheduler

---

# Job Types

- Sync Jobs
- AI Precompute Jobs
- Flashcard Scheduling Jobs
- Notification Jobs
- Analytics Batch Jobs
- Study Plan Generation Jobs

---

# Queue Strategy

- FIFO processing
- priority-based execution
- retry on failure
- exponential backoff

---

# Offline Behaviour

- jobs queued locally
- executed when online
- persistent queue storage

---

# AI Integration

AI jobs include:

- pre-generating explanations
- summarizing notes
- generating flashcards
- analyzing weak areas

---

# API Contracts

POST /jobs/create

GET /jobs/status

POST /jobs/retry

POST /jobs/cancel

---

# State Management

JobState includes:

- queued
- running
- completed
- failed
- retrying

---

# Performance Rules

- jobs must not block UI
- batch execution preferred
- limit concurrent workers

---

# Reliability Rules

- guaranteed execution
- retry logic mandatory
- no silent failures

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Queue logic

Retry system

Job execution flow

Integration Tests:

Offline job processing

AI background job execution

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating background jobs:

- always queue heavy tasks
- always allow retries
- always support offline execution
- never run heavy tasks on main thread